Equations: temp = temperature in year t econ = the fraction of economic activity that is retained in a year if the temp is temp consumption = total consumption at time t utility = societys utility from consumption Ramsey rule: o = pure rate of time preference g = growth rate of income over time n = elasticity of marginal utility of consumption with respect to income (how much more does a poor person value a dollar compared to a rich person?)

Formula for present value: net utility today = SUM[utility at year t / (1+discount_rate)^t] across all years

2.c. \(\theta\)-

When we are certain that under business as usual, T = 4.4, society is willing to give up 0.3943595 of their consumption every year for the next 200 years in order to completely prevent climate change.

Under uncertainty over T, society is willing to give up 0.3778873 of their consumption every year for the next 200 years in order to completely prevent climate change.
